## Rules

- **Single shell.** **`AppShell`** mounts once per org (or other post-login root). Use **`AppSubLayout`** for inner rails (admin, HRM) ‚Äî never nest a second full shell.
- **Registry-aligned nav.** Rail slots built from capability registries (`ORG_ADMIN_CAPABILITIES`, `HRM_CAPABILITIES`, `PLATFORM_ADMIN_CAPABILITIES`) or typed data contracts. No orphaned `NAV_ITEMS` arrays.
- **L1 widgets.** Use `WorkbenchUtilityRoundTooltipButton` / `WorkbenchUtilityRoundTooltipLink` / `WorkbenchUtilityTriggerTooltip`. Do not import `#components/ui/tooltip` directly inside `components/workbench/**`.
- **Boring shell.** No animated chrome for novelty. Density and calm ERP posture beat marketing energy.
- **Feature two-pane layouts** (Orbit queue+detail) live **inside** `WorkbenchSurface.children` under `lib/features/<module>/components/` ‚Äî not confused with shell components.

## Forbidden

- Tenant/ERP/domain logic inside `components/workbench/**`.
- Deep imports into `lib/features/<module>/data/...` from shell ‚Äî use `#features/<module>` or `#features/<module>/client`.
- Cross-tenant or slug-from-client assumptions ‚Äî org slug comes from server guards + path builders.
- Reviving `nexus-shell.tsx` / `nexus-surface-chrome.tsx` (deleted ‚Äî `WorkbenchShell` replaced them).
- New shell chrome inside `components/nexus/` ‚Äî shell belongs in `components/workbench/`.
- Creating `components/dashboard/` shell directory ‚Äî there is no second shell stack.

